  <channel>
    <title>Line of Sight issues</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&amp;message.id=12099</link>
    <description>This thread is to consolidate reports about line of sight bugs that have been popping up.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Line of sight issues I'm interested in seeing more information about include:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Targeting via clicking with mouse not working even though you are clicking right on it.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Spells that won't cast or land because you are blocked by something that really doesn't seem like it should be blocking.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Combat where you should be able to melee but can't see your target.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;The information I need in order for your post to be useful in tracking down this problem is the following:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;The zone you are in.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;If you were targeting, clicking, casting, combat, whatever.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;What race you are playing&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;If you are shrunk or levitated.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The exact coordinates you are at as shown by the /loc command.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The coordinates of your target at the time of LOS failure, which I know is going to be an approximation but as specific as you can get will really help. Within a unit or two.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The name of the NPC. This is because height affects the endpoints of the line segment used for the collision call.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comments about what appears to be blocking the LOS to the target. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;If you are able, please do me a favor and take a screenshot of the situation and include a link to it in your post. If not, that's ok, I know it's a hassle to manage images on the web. The other information is most important.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you can provide the above information, your post will be very helpful in finding more cases to reproduce this problem. Without the above information, please refrain from posting in this thread, I need to solve this problem and I need very specific data to do so and would like to avoid off topic stuff in here. I've been working on other bugs (pathing, warping, etc) and haven't had a lot of time to investigate this yet so a set of good test cases would help speed this up for me quite a bit.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;One thing I have already confirmed is that some shrubs in qvic block LOS incorrectly due to a bug that appears to have been introduced about 18 months ago. The other day I wrote a tool to scan every model in every zone in all of everquest to find all models that can possibly cause an LOS problem due to this particular bug I found. While there were a fair number of models that met the criteria, the various reports players have posted about LOS problems included a number of other zones that I have confirmed do not include models that trigger this bug. So there is something else going on in addition to the bug I found.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;There were some changes made to the LOS behavior which had to occur to support destructible object targeting &amp;amp; combat. It's likely the problems people are seeing are the result of that. I plan to do a test where I run the old code in parallel with the new code and trigger alerts when &amp;amp; if behavior is ever any different between them when dealing with regular targeting situations that don't include destructibles becuse that behavior should not have changed. With the data I hope to get from the players in this thread, I will test the various situations with this diagnostic code enabled and eventually figure out what went wrong. I have some locs to test already, but details are scarce and getting more info would be pretty helpful at this point.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Thanks for any help getting details on this problem, it's appreciated.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
