uld be able to get relatively accurate locs for this.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Was playing Human wizzy, unshrunk, on a horse, may of may not have been levved. (I prefer not to use lev, however in zones where LOS is an issue - general all to some extent, especially PoP onwards I do use it.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Old world zones are foar more target friendly than more recent expansions.&amp;nbsp; The instance with the dragon's corpse was a surprise, it has happened in other zones with npc/pc being targetted even when behind me, but this was a large distance behind me.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I would guess that as they have far more flat planes and fewer 'clutter' on the ground to be one of the reasons why.they are more target friendly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;LoS issues are usually imo the result of 'eye candy' - but when a mob is a hundred feet tall and the eye cany can be measured in the inches, being told one is not able to see a mob is ludicrous, it spoils the whole immersion experience.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;u&gt;An example of F8 and LoS issues.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I know changes were made to targetting probably some years ago now.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Before PoP was released I would multi-quad toilers in Maidens Eye.&amp;nbsp; The mainly live about the hill area towards Umbral Plains.&amp;nbsp; Running round on horse pressing F8 and using Flux Staff to pull would easily get me a pile of mobs.&amp;nbsp; Now going to ME (no I don't still experience there) and using F8 it takes longer to get the same numbers as F8 appears to require a more direct line from me to mob, and can be much more likely to trigger the 'you cant see the mob' note ( did I mention how silly that is when a hundred foot giant/dragon is stood in front of me?)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I remeber that the Flux Staff (favourite wizzy pulling item - instant click small debuffer) used to work even when the mob was totally out of LoS.&amp;nbsp; Other spells would not work but Flux Staff did.&amp;nbsp; Now Flux Staff requires the same LoS as any other spell (except pacification spells and collaboration and healing spells - maybe others).&amp;nbsp; It is these changes that have casued the issues of LoS to develope over the years.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I suspect the spot of npc delegated for LoS is probably around the feet, I suggest moving it up, waist or chest hight.&amp;nbsp; This would be more realistic, as it would allow partially hidden mobs to be pulled (only being able to see 50 feet of a hundred foot mob shouldnt make it out of sight). An alternative would be to have more than one LoS spot,&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Head, Waist, Feet, all three are checked, if one is visible, mob is in sight.&amp;nbsp; To save processor overheads on checking start with head, or waist and do feet last (if there is an&amp;nbsp; overhead with doing three checks).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;So we see mob tag it and he brings any friends we couldnt see.&amp;nbsp; Sounds like more fun and mayhem, possibly a few deaths but that is a risk we take.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
